BRIEFING:
A RIDGE JUST NORTH OF THE ISLANDS WILL BRING LIGHT AND VARIABLE WINDS STATEWIDE TODAY, WITH SEA BREEZES SETTING UP BY AFTERNOON. THE SEA BREEZES WILL RESULT IN SOME INTERIOR CLOUD BUILD UPS AND POSSIBLE BRIEF MOUNTAIN OBSCURATIONS OVER THE ISLANDS LATER TODAY, BUT VFR WILL BE THE PREVAILING CONDITION. LAND BREEZES WILL CLEAR OUT SKIES TONIGHT, FOLLOWED BY THE RETURN OF LIGHT TRADE WINDS SUNDAY.
THREAT: NO SIGMETS IN AREA OF OPERATION.
MEL-CDL M25-23-01A REQUIRED FLIGHT ATTENDANT SEATS
